Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
\{ $gwprob->print_q() \}
\{ $gwprob->print_a() \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS(radio_cmp( $gwprob->correct_ans() ));

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

Note that
\[\begin{aligned}
    ($x + $a)^2 - $asq &= $x^2 + $twoa $x + $asq - $asq\\
                       &= $x^2 + $twoa $x\\
                       &= $x ($x + $twoa) = $x ($twoa + $x).
\end{aligned}\]

Alternately, we can rewrite this as a difference of squares and
use that to do the factorization:
\[\begin{aligned}
    ($x + $a)^2 - $asq &= ($x + $a)^2 - $a^2\\
                       &= (($x + $a) - $a)(($x + $a) + $a)\\
                       &= $x ($x + $twoa).
\end{aligned}\]

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

ENDDOCUMENT();
